Metro Pacific, Philippine Telephone: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-02T00:11:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/metro-pacific-philippine-telephone-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as yesterday in
Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.5 percent to
3,784.23.    International Container Terminal Services Inc . (ICT PM):
ICTSI Warehousing Inc. bought 470,200 shares in the nation’s
largest port operator, a stock exchange filing showed. The stock
advanced 6.7 percent to 38.85 pesos.    Metro Pacific Investments Corp . (MPI PM): The Philippine
unit of Hong Kong’s First Pacific Co. plans to acquire more
hospitals, particularly in the central province of Cebu, which
is an attractive place for medical tourism, Metro Pacific
Chairman Manuel Pangilinan said. The stock increased 2 percent
to 3.50 pesos.    Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co . (TEL PM): Profit at
the nation’s biggest company by market value fell 16 percent to
8.23 billion pesos, a stock exchange filing showed. Excluding
one-time expenses related to manpower reduction, asset
impairment and foreign exchange losses, core profit increased 4
percent to 10.6 billion pesos. The stock fell 0.9 percent to
2,140 pesos.    SM Development Corp . (SMDC PM): The property company owned
by the country’s richest man, Henry Sy, will distribute 1.1
billion shares as stock dividend and its board approved to raise
its capital to 12.4 billion pesos. The stock slid 0.4 percent to
7.06 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
